<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 11:53PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A GUSTY THUNDERSHOWER WILL AFFECT CENTRAL CAMPBELL...NORTHEASTERN
BEDFORD...AND SOUTHWESTERN AMHERST COUNTIES AND THE CITY OF
LYNCHBURG...
At 1153 PM EDT, a shower was located near Goode, or near Bedford,
moving east at 20 mph.
Winds in excess of 25 mph are possible with this shower.
Locations impacted include...
Lynchburg...
Bedford...
Rustburg...
Forest...
Evington...
Coleman Falls...
and Boonsboro.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
